Ruperti thinks that a line or two may have dropped out of the text between 160 and 161. The first Punic war began U.C. 489, and lasted twenty-three years; the second lasted from U. C. 535 till 552. The third from U.C. 604 till 606, when Carthage was destroyed—Pyrrhum. This monarch was descended from Achilles by the side of his mother. and from Hercules by that of his father. He invaded Italy, and was sor a while successful against the Romans, but at length he received a severe defeat from Curius, and in consequence was forced to evacuate the country (B.C. 274).
